HEADWORD: Naughtiness
<hw>Naugh"ti*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
naughty; perverseness; badness; wickedness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I know thy pride, and the <qex>naughtiness</qex> of thine
heart.</q> <rj><qau>1 Sam. xvii. 28.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Naughtly</ent>⟦br⟧
